---
// Ecofonts landing page. The drop zone stashes the file in IndexedDB
// (src/lib/handoff.ts) and redirects to /font, which picks it up.
---

<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
		<meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
		<meta
			name="description"
			content="Ecofonts punches microscopic holes into your fonts so they print with less ink. 100% in your browser — your files never leave your computer."
		/>
		<title>Ecofonts — Save Ink, Save the planet</title>
	</head>
	<body>
		<nav>
			<a class="brand" href="/">
				<img src="/favicon.svg" alt="Ecofonts logo" width="36" height="36" />
				<span>Ecofonts</span>
			</a>
			<a class="btn" href="/font">Open the optimizer</a>
		</nav>

		<header class="hero">
			<h1>Save Ink, <span class="accent">Save the planet</span></h1>
			<p class="tagline">
				Ecofonts punches microscopic holes into every letter of your fonts and PDFs. Your
				documents look the same — your printer uses up to 20% less ink.
			</p>

			<div
				id="dropzone"
				role="button"
				tabindex="0"
				aria-label="Drop a .ttf, .zip or .pdf file here, or press Enter to browse"
			>
				<img src="/favicon.svg" alt="" width="48" height="48" />
				<p><strong>Drop your font or PDF here</strong></p>
				<p class="hint">.ttf, .zip or .pdf — or click to browse</p>
				<input id="drop-input" type="file" accept=".ttf,.zip,.pdf" hidden />
			</div>
			<p id="drop-error" role="alert" hidden>
				Please choose a .ttf font, a .zip archive, or a .pdf document.
			</p>
			<p class="privacy">Everything runs in your browser. Your font never leaves your computer.</p>
		</header>

		<main>
			<section>
				<h2>How it works</h2>
				<div class="grid three">
					<article class="card">
						<span class="step">1</span>
						<h3>Upload</h3>
						<p>
							Drop a <code>.ttf</code> file, a whole <code>.zip</code> font family — like the
							ones you download from Google Fonts — or a <code>.pdf</code> document.
						</p>
					</article>
					<article class="card">
						<span class="step">2</span>
						<h3>Tune</h3>
						<p>
							Pick your Eco Intensity from 1% to 20% and preview the result before and after,
							right in the page.
						</p>
					</article>
					<article class="card">
						<span class="step">3</span>
						<h3>Download</h3>
						<p>
							Get your optimized font back with the same file name and folder structure, ready
							to install and print with.
						</p>
					</article>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="alt">
				<h2>Why Ecofonts?</h2>
				<div class="grid four">
					<article class="card">
						<h3>🔒 Private by design</h3>
						<p>
							No uploads, no servers, no accounts. The processing happens entirely on your
							machine.
						</p>
					</article>
					<article class="card">
						<h3>✒️ Real ink savings</h3>
						<p>
							The intensity you choose is the ink you save — we measure the actual area removed
							from every glyph, not a marketing number.
						</p>
					</article>
					<article class="card">
						<h3>👓 Invisible at print size</h3>
						<p>
							The holes are tiny and never touch the outline of a letter, so text stays crisp
							and legible at reading sizes.
						</p>
					</article>
					<article class="card">
						<h3>📦 Family-friendly</h3>
						<p>
							Zip archives keep their exact structure — every weight and style inside gets
							optimized, licenses and readmes ride along untouched.
						</p>
					</article>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section id="faq">
				<h2>FAQ</h2>
				<details>
					<summary>How does this work?</summary>
					<p>
						Ecofonts reads the vector outlines of every glyph in your font, then subtracts a
						fine grid of tiny holes from the interior of each letter using boolean geometry —
						the same kind of operation vector editors use. The outer silhouette of every letter
						is left untouched, so shapes stay recognizable. The modified outlines are compiled
						back into a font file you can install anywhere.
					</p>
				</details>
				<details>
					<summary>Does this work completely on my computer?</summary>
					<p>
						Yes — 100%. There is no server: parsing, geometry, and packaging all run in your
						browser. Your font file is never uploaded anywhere, and the page even works offline
						once it has loaded.
					</p>
				</details>
				<details>
					<summary>Which files are supported?</summary>
					<p>
						A single <code>.ttf</code> font, a <code>.zip</code> archive containing
						<code>.ttf</code> fonts — including nested folders such as the
						<code>static/</code> directory in Google Fonts downloads — or a
						<code>.pdf</code> document. Archives come back with their exact structure
						preserved.
					</p>
				</details>
				<details>
					<summary>Can I optimize a whole PDF?</summary>
					<p>
						Yes. Drop a <code>.pdf</code> and Ecofonts finds every TrueType font embedded in
						the document, punches the eco holes into its glyphs, and rebuilds the file. The
						layout, images, and text stay exactly as they were — the text even remains
						selectable. Fonts embedded in other formats (Type 1/CFF) are left unchanged, and
						you'll see a note when that happens.
					</p>
				</details>
				<details>
					<summary>Will my text still look good?</summary>
					<p>
						Yes. A minimum "wall" of ink is always preserved around every hole, so the edges of
						each letter stay solid and sharp. At typical reading sizes the holes are too small
						to notice — they simply let your printer skip ink the eye never misses.
					</p>
				</details>
				<details>
					<summary>How much ink can I actually save?</summary>
					<p>
						The Eco Intensity slider goes from 1% to 20%, and it maps to the real share of
						printed area removed from the letters — at 15% intensity, roughly 15% less ink goes
						on the page for the same text.
					</p>
				</details>
				<details>
					<summary>What about variable fonts?</summary>
					<p>
						Variable fonts are processed as their default style, and you'll see a note when
						that happens. For a full family (Bold, Light, Italic…), upload the whole zip — the
						fixed-weight fonts in its <code>static/</code> folder carry every style through.
					</p>
				</details>
				<details>
					<summary>Am I allowed to modify a font?</summary>
					<p>
						That depends on the font's license. Open licenses like the SIL Open Font License
						explicitly allow modification. For commercial fonts, check your license terms
						first. Since nothing leaves your computer, Ecofonts itself never redistributes
						anything.
					</p>
				</details>
			</section>
		</main>

		<footer>
			<img src="/favicon.svg" alt="" width="24" height="24" />
			<p>Ecofonts — fonts that print lighter. Runs entirely in your browser.</p>
		</footer>

		<script>
			import { stashFile } from "../lib/handoff";

			const zone = document.getElementById("dropzone");
			const input = document.getElementById("drop-input") as HTMLInputElement | null;
			const error = document.getElementById("drop-error");

			async function send(file: File | undefined): Promise<void> {
				if (!file || !/\.(ttf|zip|pdf)$/i.test(file.name)) {
					error?.removeAttribute("hidden");
					return;
				}
				error?.setAttribute("hidden", "");
				try {
					await stashFile(file);
				} catch {
					// If storage fails the user can simply re-pick the file on /font.
				}
				window.location.href = "/font";
			}

			if (zone && input) {
				zone.addEventListener("click", () => input.click());
				zone.addEventListener("keydown", (event) => {
					if (event.key === "Enter" || event.key === " ") {
						event.preventDefault();
						input.click();
					}
				});
				input.addEventListener("change", () => void send(input.files?.[0]));
				zone.addEventListener("dragover", (event) => {
					event.preventDefault();
					zone.classList.add("dragover");
				});
				zone.addEventListener("dragleave", () => zone.classList.remove("dragover"));
				zone.addEventListener("drop", (event) => {
					event.preventDefault();
					zone.classList.remove("dragover");
					void send(event.dataTransfer?.files?.[0]);
				});
			}
		</script>

		<style>
			:root {
				--green: #01bf63;
				--green-dark: #019a50;
				--green-tint: #e9faf1;
				--ink: #12211a;
				--muted: #5b6b62;
				--line: #e3ece7;
			}
			* {
				box-sizing: border-box;
			}
			body {
				margin: 0;
				font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, "Segoe UI", sans-serif;
				color: var(--ink);
				background: #fff;
				line-height: 1.6;
			}

			nav {
				display: flex;
				align-items: center;
				justify-content: space-between;
				max-width: 1040px;
				margin: 0 auto;
				padding: 16px 24px;
			}
			.brand {
				display: flex;
				align-items: center;
				gap: 10px;
				text-decoration: none;
				color: var(--ink);
				font-weight: 700;
				font-size: 1.25rem;
			}
			.btn {
				background: var(--green);
				color: #fff;
				text-decoration: none;
				font-weight: 600;
				padding: 10px 20px;
				border-radius: 999px;
				transition: background 0.15s;
			}
			.btn:hover {
				background: var(--green-dark);
			}

			.hero {
				max-width: 720px;
				margin: 0 auto;
				padding: 48px 24px 64px;
				text-align: center;
			}
			h1 {
				font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 5.5vw, 3.4rem);
				line-height: 1.15;
				margin: 0 0 16px;
			}
			.accent {
				color: var(--green);
			}
			.tagline {
				font-size: 1.15rem;
				color: var(--muted);
				margin: 0 auto 36px;
				max-width: 560px;
			}

			#dropzone {
				max-width: 520px;
				margin: 0 auto;
				padding: 40px 24px;
				border: 2px dashed var(--green);
				border-radius: 16px;
				background: var(--green-tint);
				cursor: pointer;
				transition:
					background 0.15s,
					transform 0.15s,
					box-shadow 0.15s;
			}
			#dropzone:hover,
			#dropzone:focus-visible,
			#dropzone.dragover {
				background: #d9f5e7;
				transform: translateY(-2px);
				box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(1, 191, 99, 0.18);
				outline: none;
			}
			#dropzone p {
				margin: 8px 0 0;
			}
			#dropzone .hint {
				color: var(--muted);
				font-size: 0.95rem;
			}
			#drop-error {
				color: #b00020;
				margin-top: 12px;
			}
			.privacy {
				margin-top: 20px;
				font-size: 0.9rem;
				color: var(--muted);
			}

			main section {
				padding: 64px 24px;
			}
			main section.alt {
				background: #f6fbf8;
				border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
				border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
			}
			h2 {
				text-align: center;
				font-size: 2rem;
				margin: 0 0 40px;
			}
			.grid {
				display: grid;
				gap: 20px;
				max-width: 1040px;
				margin: 0 auto;
			}
			.grid.three {
				grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
			}
			.grid.four {
				grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
			}
			.card {
				background: #fff;
				border: 1px solid var(--line);
				border-radius: 12px;
				padding: 24px;
			}
			.card h3 {
				margin: 0 0 8px;
				font-size: 1.1rem;
			}
			.card p {
				margin: 0;
				color: var(--muted);
				font-size: 0.97rem;
			}
			.step {
				display: inline-flex;
				align-items: center;
				justify-content: center;
				width: 32px;
				height: 32px;
				border-radius: 50%;
				background: var(--green);
				color: #fff;
				font-weight: 700;
				margin-bottom: 12px;
			}

			#faq {
				max-width: 720px;
				margin: 0 auto;
			}
			details {
				border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
				padding: 4px 0;
			}
			summary {
				cursor: pointer;
				font-weight: 600;
				padding: 14px 0;
				list-style-position: inside;
			}
			summary:hover {
				color: var(--green-dark);
			}
			details p {
				margin: 0 0 16px;
				color: var(--muted);
			}

			footer {
				display: flex;
				flex-direction: column;
				align-items: center;
				gap: 8px;
				padding: 40px 24px;
				border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
				color: var(--muted);
				font-size: 0.9rem;
			}
			footer p {
				margin: 0;
			}
		</style>
	</body>
</html>
